      "role": "user",
      "content": "i feel like calling it just \"ambiguity\" kind of ignores the fact that one side is actually trying to stick to the law and the other is just trying to change it to whatever they want. if the text is right there, isn't it just a fact that the originalist view is the only legitimate way to interpret the constitution? isn't it basically just incorrect to say otherwise?",
